The paper deals with the design of precoding and combining matrices for initial downlink synchronization in millimeter wave massive MIMO systems. This involves signal processing, communication theory, and network architecture, which are all covered by the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Multimedia (cs.MM), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Computer Communications (cs.COM) sub-categories. However, since the paper focuses on the synchronization aspect, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.MM, cs.SY, and cs.COM.
